rules: Rule1: If the conservation bill is approved, then provided that a natural habitat does not exist, the plant species is protected.
Rule2: In the event that the senate vote is passed, the conservation bill is approved.
Rule3: Either the senate vote is passed or the house vote is passed.
Rule4: Should the house vote be passed, the conservation bill becomes approved.
Rule5: Given that the environmental group is supported, the conservation program is funded.
Rule6: The environmental group is supported or the scientific community is supported.
Rule7: Provided that the scientific community is supported, then whenever it is false that lacking a natural habitat leads to the plant species being protected, the national park is not designated.

Rule8: If the conservation program is funded, then in the case that it is not true that the non-existence of a natural habitat results in the plant species being protected, the national park is not designated.
Rule9: Assuming that it is not the case that the absence of a natural habitat implies the plant species is protected, the national park is designated.
facts: Fact1: It is not the case that the plant species is protected.
